quran[96]{c,v,t}:
  56,1,When there happeneth Event
  56,2,There is about its happening no lie
  56,3,Abasing exalting
  56,4,"This will happen when the earth is shaken, shaken"
  56,5,"And the mountains are crumbled, crumbled"
  56,6,So that they become dust seattered
  56,7,And ye are classes three
  56,8,Those on the right hand; how happy shall those on the right hand be
  56,9,And those on the left hand; how miserable shall those on the left hand be
  56,10,And the preceders are the pre-ceders
  56,11,Those! they shall be the brought nigh
  56,12,In Gardens of Delight
  56,13,A multitude from the ancients
  56,14,And a few from the later generations
  56,15,On couches in wrought with gold
  56,16,Reclining thereon facing each other
  56,17,There shall go round Unto them youths ever-young
  56,18,With goblets and ewers and a cup of limpid drink
  56,19,Whereby there shall be neither headiness nor will they be inebriated
  56,20,And with fruit from that which they choose
  56,21,And with flesh of fowls from that Which they desire
  56,22,And there will be fair ones large eyed
  56,23,The likes Unto pearls hidden
  56,24,A recompense for that which they have been working
  56,25,Therein they hear no vain or sinful discourse
  56,26,"Nought but the saying: peace! peace"
  56,27,And the fellows on the right hand; how be happy shall the fellows on the right hand be
  56,28,Midst lote-trees thornless
  56,29,And plantains laden with fruit
  56,30,And a shade ever-spread
  56,31,And water everflowing
  56,32,And fruit abundant
  56,33,Neither ending nor forbidden
  56,34,And carpets raised
  56,35,Verily We! We have created those maidens by a creation
  56,36,And have made them virgins
  56,37,"Loving, of equal age"
  56,38,For the fellows on the right hand
  56,39,A multitude from the ancients
  56,40,And a multitude from the later generations
  56,41,And the fellows on the left hand; how miserable Shall the fellows on the left hand be
  56,42,Amidst scorching wind and scalding water
  56,43,And the shade of black smoke
  56,44,Neither cool nor pleasant
  56,45,Verily they have been heretofore affluent
  56,46,And they have been persisting in the heinous offence
  56,47,"And they were wont to say: when we have died and become dust and bones, shall we, then, verily be raised"
  56,48,We and our fathers of old
  56,49,"Say thou: verily the ancients and those of later generations"
  56,50,Are going to be assembled on the appointed time of a Day Known
  56,51,"Then verily ye, O ye erring, denying people"
  56,52,Shall surely eat of the tree of Az-Zqqum
  56,53,And shall fill therewith your bellies
  56,54,And shall be drinkers thereon of boiling water
  56,55,Drinkers even as the drinking of thirsty camels
  56,56,This shall be their entertainment on the Day of Requital
  56,57,"We! it is We Who created you: wherefore confess ye not"
  56,58,Behold! - that which ye emit
  56,59,"Create him ye, or are We the Creator"
  56,60,We! it is We Who have decreed death Unto you all. And We are not to be outrun
  56,61,That We may substitute others like Unto you and produce you into that which ye know not
  56,62,And assuredly ye have fully known the first Production Wherefore heed ye not
  56,63,Behold! - that which ye sow
  56,64,"Cause it ye to grow, or are We the Grower"
  56,65,"If We willed, surely We would make it chaff, so that ye would be left wondering"
  56,66,Verily we are undone
  56,67,Aye! we are deprived
  56,68,Behold! - the water which ye drink
  56,69,"Send it down ye from the raincloud, or are We the Sender down"
  56,70,"If We willed, surely We would make it brackish. Wherefore give ye not thanks"
  56,71,Behold! - the fire which ye strike out
  56,72,"Produce ye the tree thereof, or are We the Producer"
  56,73,We! it is We Who made it a reminder and a provision Unto the campers
  56,74,"Wherefore hallow thou the name of thy Lord, the Mighty"
  56,75,I swear by the setting of the stars
  56,76,"And verily that is a mighty oath, if ye but knew"
  56,77,That it is a Recitation honourable
  56,78,In a Book Hidden
  56,79,Which none can touch except the purified
  56,80,It is a revelation from the Lord of the worlds
  56,81,Is it this discourse that ye hold lightly
  56,82,And make it your provision that ye should belie it
  56,83,Wherefore then - when the soul cometh up to the wind-pipe
  56,84,And ye are then looking on
  56,85,"And We are nigher Unto him than ye are, but ye behold not"
  56,86,"Wherefore then, if ye are not to be requited"
  56,87,"Cause ye it not to return, if ye say sooth"
  56,88,Then if he be of the broughtnigh
  56,89,"For him shall be comfort, and fragrance and a Garden of Delight"
  56,90,And if he be of the fellows on the right hand
  56,91,"Then: peace Unto thee, for thou art of those on the right hand"
  56,92,"And if he be of the beliers, the erring"
  56,93,Then an entertainment of boiling water
  56,94,And roasting in a Blaze
  56,95,Verily this! this is the very truth
  56,96,"Wherefore hallow thou the name of thy Lord, the Mighty"